 people of a man called Hwīta or Witta’, from the Old English personal name <i>Hwīta</i> (or <i>Witta</i> in the Suffolk name) + the Old English group name suffix <i>-ingas</i> (genitive <i>-inga-</i>) + <i>hām</i> ‘village, homestead’. The name may also derive from Wittenham (Berkshire), which is named from the Old English personal name <i>Witta</i> (genitive <i>Wittan</i>) + Old English <i>hamm</i> ‘water meadow’. This surname is also found in Wales.","History: Richand Whittingham and his son, also called Richard, brass founders from Birmingham, Warwickshire, England, came to New York City in 1791, where they established a successful business."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Alan","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Of Celtic origin and uncertain derivation (possibly a diminutive of a word meaning ‘rock’). It was introduced into England by  Breton  followers of  William the Conqueror , most notably  Alan , Earl of Brittany, who was rewarded for his services with vast estates in the newly conquered kingdom. In Britain the variants  <b>Allan</b>  and  <b>Allen</b>  are considerably less frequent, and generally represent transferred uses of surname forms, whereas in America all three forms of the name are approximately equally common.  See also  Alun ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Alan Whittingham was born in 1354, in England, United Kingdom. He had at least 1 son with Catherine."},"et":{"1354–":"1354–Surnud","1360–1431":"1360–1431","1386–Male":"1386–Surnud","1354–Male":"1354–Surnud","22 December 1386":"22. detsember 1386","1354":"1354","1431":"1431","1386":"1386","1360":"1360","Manchester, Lancashire, England":"Manchester, Lancashire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1354–":"1354–Kuollut","1360–1431":"1360–1431","1386–Male":"1386–Kuollut","1354–Male":"1354–Kuollut","22 December 1386":"22. joulukuuta 1386","1354":"1354","1431":"1431","1386":"138